## Configuration Management
- **ALWAYS** use centralized configuration loading
- **ALWAYS** validate configuration on startup
- **ALWAYS** provide sensible defaults for development
- **ALWAYS** use environment variables for sensitive data
- **ALWAYS** document all configuration options

## Environment Handling
- **ALWAYS** support multiple environments (dev, staging, prod)
- **ALWAYS** use different configs per environment
- **ALWAYS** never hardcode environment-specific values
- **ALWAYS** use configuration files for non-sensitive data
- **ALWAYS** validate required configuration on startup

